## Other information

Since `event.keyCode` is marked as deprecated,  `@angular/cdk/keycodes` should export key as string values to so they can be compared with either `event.key` or `event.code`

#### What is the expected behavior?

 `@angular/cdk/keycodes` should exports string value instead of number so it can be compared with `event.keyCode`

#### What is the current behavior?

It works, but the keyboard's `event.keyCode` is marked as deprecated

#### What are the steps to reproduce?

For example:
```ts
import { ESCAPE } from '@angular/cdk/keycodes';

// Close on escape click
 this._overlayRef.keydownEvents().subscribe((event: KeyboardEvent) => {
   if (event.keyCode === ESCAPE) {
     this.close();
   }
 });
```


#### Which versions of Angular, Material, OS, TypeScript, browsers are affected?

Material@7.2.2

#### What is the expected behavior?
As shown in documentation examples, the class ```mat-sort-header-sorted``` should allow override of the default header styles for the sorted header cell.

#### What is the current behavior?
CSS selector mat-sort-header-sorted has no effect when specified.  From the documentation example:
```
th.mat-sort-header-sorted {
  color: black;
}
```
#### What are the steps to reproduce?
The StackBlitz provided by the official documentation (https://material.angular.io/components/sort/overview) shows the issue:
https://stackblitz.com/angular/byxxpgxkqkl?file=app%2Ftable-sorting-example.css

#### Which versions of Angular, Material, OS, TypeScript, browsers are affected?
7.7.2.  Tested in current release versions of Chrome and Edge

#### Is there anything else we should know?
A stack overflow article (https://stackoverflow.com/questions/54278026/style-mat-sort-header-sorted-has-no-effect-in-mat-table-tutorial) suggested using ```::ng-deep```.  This does work but as ng-deep is deprecated, it should not be the proper way to style a sorted header column in a mat-table.

This does work for now:
::ng-deep .mat-sort-header-sorted {
  color: black;
}
